translated: Fries, Elias Harald, practical doctor, Gothenburg, born on December 27th, 1878 in Gothenburg to medical doctor Robert F. and Sofia Elisabet Bergman. Married in 23 years with Anna Carlander. Completed his Master's degree in Gothenburg in 1896, Bachelor of Science in Uppsala in 1897 and Bachelor of Medicine there in 1901, Medical degree in Stockholm in 1906. Temporary epidemic doctor in Uppsala in 1905, assistant physician at Kristinehamns hospital in 1906, at Karlstad's Hospital from 1906-1908, assistant and second physician at Sahlgren's Hospital from 1908-1910, temporary district doctor and physician at Stampen Lung Hospital in Gothenburg from 1913-1922, temporary inspector physician in Gothenburg district for short periods annually from 1920-1923 and 1924-1926, iron-refinery physician from 1917-1943, physician at Gothenburg primary school from 1921-1943, official vaccinator in Gothenburg in 1926, practical doctor in Gothenburg. Member of the board of directors for Gothenburg's tree society. Publications include "Gothenburg's and Bohemia's fern and fern allies" (1945) and articles on botanical subjects. Hobby: botany. Received the Order of Vasa.
